  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b92\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A united declaration to win the struggle",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The declaration event of the conference organized by all party activists on the theme \u201cDeclaration of Victory in the Struggle\u201d took place at Colombo Ramada Hotel on Wednesday (06).",
        "The declaration to win the struggle included six specific features and the all-party militants said they would dedicate themselves to its success.",
        "The leader of the opposition expressed his appreciation for the efforts of the militants to establish a democratic regime in the country and take the country forward, and he said that he agrees with all its democratic demands without any objection.",
        "The Leader of the Opposition said that executive power is not limited to the President and he said that his executive power also extends to the Legislative Assembly. Therefore, the leader of the opposition said that he has a fixed opinion regarding the abolition of the office of the president with executive powers, and he said that all the groups involved in the struggle should join together and contribute to the journey of building the country."
      ],
